The paper discusses the integration of RF and millimeter wave technologies for 5G cellular systems, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of complex algorithms for tracking channel variations and adjusting resources, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a beamforming scheme for the millimeter wave interface, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses experimentation in indoor and outdoor settings, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a scheduling algorithm to maximize the delay-constrained throughput, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
